node.text:
Never give up 👊 You can check how to get your photos promoted in our page, use the link in our bio: @RunningTerritory

Not sure I’ve ever had an experience like this one before. In the weeks leading up to the Games, I had to fight constant doubt - in myself, my abilities, my resilience - all of it.

I went into this event knowing I had never even pressed the required weight before. To get it once would be a PR. I was embarrassed, exhausted and emotionally drained.

This entire week, my coach @iamprofithh85 told me over and over, “you have to believe in yourself. You cannot do any of this unless you believe in yourself.”

No joke, about 3 minutes into the 11min event I looked up at Scooter after several fails. He was screaming at me, “Amy you gotta believe. You HAVE to believe.” It’s what made me get that freaking bar over my head throughout the workout.

This entire week was nothing like I thought it would be. Turns out, it wasn’t about the competition for me. It wasn’t even about working out. It was about me learning to truly believe in myself.

I have no idea what the future holds, but I’m excited to keep going. 🙌

📽 @maurorider
🏋️‍♀️ @onelegtostandon

"Just to remember that the ideal moment does not exist. Either you regret doing it or not doing it. You will never be able to change something that has already happened. Be happy, make mistakes, and learn.

Good weekend and good training!! 🏃🏽‍♀️💪🏼"

📽 @thalya_hill

Endurance training 💦 Wanna see your content posted in our account? Apply for a feature on runningterritory.com/feature (link in my bio: @RunningTerritory) 

Chipper WODs 💪
⏱FOR TIME⏱
•100 doubleunders
•90 air squats
•80 situps
•70 mountain climbers
•60 lunges
•50 handstand shoulder taps
•40 KB swings
•30 push press
•20 hang squat cleans
•10 power snatch
——
👉🏼suggested weights: (male/female): KB(32/24kg) BB(135/95#)
👉🏼complete listed reps before moving on to the next movement
👉🏼for mtn climbers and lunges: left leg + right leg =1 rep.
👉🏼strength/skill beforehand: RDLs and hip banded work
🌒🌕🌘

📽 @alexislunarbody

node.text:
The best leg ever 🐶🦵We can post your photos and videos in our account, follow the link in our bio @RunningTerritory and we will select your pictures.

Tag someone who has to see this!

This is the story of Andrea Pusateri, a paralympic athlete and his adorable dog Sally:

"At the age of three and a half, I escaped from my mother’s hands while a train was passing at the Monza’s train station. She laid down her life to save me and I lost both of my legs, but the doctors were able to reimplant my left leg with an operation. When I was a child, I practiced several sports until I run into the bicycle. In 2008, I began my agonistic carrier in the Paralympic world, where I achieved several results at a national and international level."

How awe-inspiring is Andrea's story? 🐶

📽 @pusateriandrea
📍Cancano Lake, Italy
🎶 Tommee Profitt - In The End (Mellen Gi Remix) [feat. Fleurie]
